reviews.text: super easy and delicious!
Super easy to prepare and everyone at my dinner party loved them. They went very quickly!
These are awesome! I only had the batter sit for about 10 minutes and added flax meal and walnuts. Thumbs up!!
I added walnuts.... delicious!!!

Wow these are so good. I made them for dinner on Friday night and we both loved them. I scaled the recipe for 2 servings and made more sauce, per other reviewers suggestions. I will definitely make this again!
These bars are so easy to prepare and so delicious. I added sliced almonds to the crust/topping for a little added protein and texture and everyone loved them.
Super easy to make and super delicious. I added about 1 cup sliced almonds for a little extra protein. It was great!
Such a great recipe. I caramelized the onions for about 30 minutes before browning the chicken for a richer flavor, added half the honey, and used parsley instead of cilantro. A major crowd-pleaser!
Super easy and delicious!
I used homemade cornbread mix and just jalapeños, skipping cheese and bacon. Delicious!!!
Made this last night and turned out really well! I cooked it for about 15 minutes longer, increasing heat to 350 at the end. Nice a crisp on the outside, tender on the inside.
I made these exactly as written (except for walnut milk instead of cow's milk) and turned out perfectly!
This was such a great recipe! I made these for Thanksgiving as an alternative to turkey. Super easy and the gravy is so good.

recipe.title: Cornish Game Hens with Garlic and Rosemary

reviews.text: I wanted to whip up a batch of pancakes over the weekend and after looking up recipes, saw that I had everything in this recipe. Super easy to make and super fluffy!
I made these twice this weekend due to a chocolate craving at night! So easy to make and I was happy to find that I had all the ingredients on hand already!
These are perfectly flaky and buttery with a nice smoky finish!
Super easy to make and a delicious way to start the day!

These were a great appetizer for a dinner party I had. I had to cook them for 30 minutes, increasing the temperature to 400 after about 20 minutes in order for them to become crisp. I will make them again!
Excellent!! I used only apples because peaches weren't available. And doubled the jalapeño. A winner in my house!

recipe.title: Eric's Grilled Pork on Pork Rollatini

reviews.text: Such a great fall dessert! I made this two times this week!
Excellent! I added roasted cauliflower, pistachios instead of pecans, and queso fresco. Yum!
Wow these are so good! My brother inhaled them!!
Crowd-pleaser at my house! I used spinach and bok choy instead of arugula and tossed in some walnuts in addition to the almonds. Yum!!
This was excellent! So easy to prepare and perfectly juicy and tender. I added chicken broth to the drippings for basting.
The generous amount of lemon juice really adds a tangy kick to the broccoli. This is one of those recipes to keep as a quick go-to for a fancy vegetable when you have company.
This is a great, homemade weeknight meal. I don't usually make cream sauce, but this one was really nice. And the peppers and onions add a nice crunch to the dish.

recipe.title: Nikki's Pork Chops with a Mushroom Cream Sauce over White Jasmine Rice

reviews.text: This cupcakes are a fun way to add some fruit and vegetables during the Halloween season! I usually avoid food coloring, so next time I will probably puree some cooked sweet potato for the frosting and use chocolate syrup to decorate instead of the gel.

recipe.title: Ann's Chocolate Chip Carrot Cake Pumpkins

reviews.text: This is a fun and creative cake to make for Halloween. The cookies for tombstones is a great idea. I liked the cake, but will probably use less sugar in the cake and the icing next time.

This recipe has a nice light flavor. I might even add double the amount of liqueur next time. Cauliflower rice is my new favorite vegetable and hadn't thought of serving it with tofu...so I am glad to have a new dish to add to my weeknight dinners.
The meatballs really have a lot of good flavor...I could really taste the soy sauce. This is a quick and easy, comfort food for busy weeknights.
The refried beans were my favorite part of this recipe...so flavorful. I wouldn't have thought to season them, but it really made a difference. And the homemade salsa really topped it all off!

This is the perfect brunch for a crowd. The spinach, bacon, egg, and cheese combo were so delicious. I love how you cut the bread and everyone gets an egg-in-the-hole sandwich! I will be trying all types of combinations every time I make it!
This is a recipe I will make over and over again. It is loaded with protein, flavor, and color. The homemade tzatziki sauce really made the dish!

Quick...easy...and a simple appetizer especially during the holidays. I loved the fresh pesto with the prosciutto. Next time I will crisp up the prosciutto under the broiler before layering it on top. Delicious!
I would have never thought to add shrimp or other proteins to cornbread...but what a great way to get extra protein! This was a crowd-pleaser!
Wow this recipe is super easy to make and at the same time looks really fancy. The potatoes have a nice crispy coating before biting into a tender center. This is a perfect date night dinner!

recipe.title: Jacob's Grilled Cajun Salmon with Roasted Fingerling Potatoes

reviews.text: The miso glaze added just the right amount of flavor to the salmon. And the green beans were perfectly tender and added a nice color to the plate.

recipe.title: Carrie's Salmon with Purple Pureed Potatoes and French Green Beans

reviews.text: I frequently make kimchi fried for dinner, but hadn't ever thought of topping it with chicken. ..loved it! Next time I will add a fried egg!

recipe.title: Troy's Korean Glazed Chicken Breast with Kimchee Fried Rice

reviews.text: I really loved the flavors in the chile-ginger sauce...such a fresh and creative way to prepare chicken breast. The fresh vegetables on the top added a nice crunch too!

recipe.title: Jackie's Lemongrass Ginger Chile Chicken and Rice

reviews.text: This is a great, quick and easy meal to make on busy weeknights. Just the right amount of ground beef, veggies, and sauce.
I have made these a handful of times and everyone always loves them. They are very flavorful!

I made this to go along with lamb kabobs and everyone loved it. I don't think my potatoes got as crisp as Chef John's because I don't think I cooked them long enough. So next time I will cook them a little longer before adding the rice to the potatoes. I will definitely be making this again!
Omgee this is good. I added jalapeño and corn to the batter. Served it with black bean soup. Yum!!!
This was a real hit at my house. I didn't have the cooking sauce, so I used homemade red chile salsa and wow did my family like it!

recipe.title: Drowned Beef Sandwich with Chipotle Sauce (Torta Ahogada)

reviews.text: This was a winner at my house last night. We wanted something light, yet filling and here it was!
These were sooo good! I used Mexican crema instead of Gruyere... Delicious!

This was so quick and easy to make. I cut the pieces really small (like the size of pencil erasers) so you get all the ingredients in each bite. I used 1/2 cup oj and 1 1/2cup water instead of 2cups oj. Delicious!
I also cooked the stalks and leaves, which were tender and crispy! This recipe gets 10 stars. So so so good! I will be making again.
So glad to know how to make grilled artichokes now! This was super easy and all of our guests loved them! We dipped them in hot sauce.
Super easy and delicious! This is a great summer dish for barbeques!
This was a great addition to a fresh summer salad. We served it in small cups to drink as an appetizer.
This was such a refreshing salad, perfect at our potluck!
So quick and so easy! I used a few heavy dashes cayenne pepper instead of the chipotle. Spicy and delicious!
This was so good! I made for dessert after bbq ... Everyone loved it. I added nectarines to the skewers!

recipe.title: Pineapple and Mango Skewers with Coconut Dip

reviews.text: This was a great opportunity to use leftover carrots, onion, celery, potatoes, and ground beef in the fridge. I skipped tomato part and peas... And added kale and parsley. Crowd-pleaser in our house!
This was a crowd-pleaser!

recipe.title: Gobi Aloo (Indian Style Cauliflower with Potatoes)

reviews.text: These are great. I made a batch to go with fried chicken and corn. I cooked them in a steaming basket and that made extra crisp on the bottom.
This is such a great, quick and easy dinner with a lot of flavor! I steamed the zoodles and turned out really well!
So incredibly flavorful and easy to make!
The vanilla really gives the almond milk an extra boost of flavor.
Omg this is such a great recipe. My boyfriend and I made this tonight and loved loved loved it. I put hard-boiled eggs in it with fresh tomatoes instead of crushed. Thank you for this awesome recipe!
Super easy and delicious! I used ham steak in place of sausage and was great.
I added garbanzo beans and hard-boiled egg for extra protein! So so good!
I used coconut cream and maple syrup instead of sweetened condensed milk and it was creamy and delicious!
Such a great dish. I used almonds in place of peanuts and added caramelized onions. Delicious!
This was so delicious! My boyfriend went back for seconds. The buttery wine sauce totally makes the dish.
Super easy to make and delicious. I didn't have self-rising flour, so I used the recipe on Allrecipes for homemade self-rising flour (just flour with baking powder and salt) and it worked out well!
This is my go-to dinner recipe. I make it without the lemon juice and it is deee-licious! I put a fried egg on top for a meal.
I made this for dessert for my boyfriend and his parents. It was a huge success! Made good leftovers for breakfast the next day.
Had this for a girl's brunch. Delicious!
So quick and easy and always impresses my guests.
We made it with ground pork and everyone loved it!
This was so easy and incredibly delicious. We cooked a 2 1/2 pound shoulder and it took 3 hours. Served with cornbread and avocado-red cabbage slaw.
I used all milk instead orange juice and challah bread. A crowd-pleaser for Mother's Day!
We used walnuts instead of pecans and added garlic. Delicious!

The flavor is excellent! We like our cauliflower really tender, so we ended up cooking it for closer to 1 hour. I increased the heat to 450 degrees F for the last 10 minutes of cooking, and it turned nicely browned. I brushed the oil mixture onto the outside about 3 times during cooking.
This was everyone's favorite dish at Thanksgiving this year.

recipe.title: Awesome Sausage, Apple and Cranberry Stuffing

reviews.text: The rosemary really added a nice flavor!
Super easy and made a delicious crust.
Delicious! And everyone loved it. Even better next day for breakfast :)
I made this last night for 4 people with a side of couscous with dates and almonds and it was a hit! Made for really good leftovers the next day for lunch.
I substituted coconut oil for the vegetable oil and increased the oats (1 cup oats, 1/2 cup ground oats) and decreased the flour to 1 1/2 cups. They were a crowd-pleaser!
Such a crowd-pleaser! I used feta and walnuts instead and drizzled about 1 tablespoon each of honey and butter over the top before roasting.

recipe.title: Roasted Dates Stuffed with Pine Nuts in Honey

reviews.text: Delicious! I didn't have apple butter, so I puréed an apple in the blender with lemon juice and cinnamon and used that in place of the apple butter and chopped apple.
This was worth all the basting ;) It was the first thing to go at a brunch this morning. Tastes like a bacon donut!
These are so easy to make and were a hit in our family and at a potluck!
Really delicious, quick, and easy! I only had powdered ginger and tastes just great!
So decadently delicious !
Such a good combination with crackers and mozzarella cheese!
This was a hit at the party and super easy to prepare. I skipped the flour because I was cooking for some gluten-free friends and thickened the sauce with cornstarch at the end. Delicious!
I did half pistachio and half pecan for the topping!
These were so good and tasted like sweet potato fries!
Such a fun and easy dessert to prepare for parties. Everyone loved them!
I needed to do something with my pile of zucchini this weekend, so seeing the video on Sunday morning was perfect timing...and I had everything on hand! Delicious!
I tried this recipe this weekend, and it was super easy to make and was a crowd-pleaser! I served with crackers and apples.
This is the most versatile 1-ingredient recipe I have ever seen. Thanks for the inspiration!
I cooked this for my dad last weekend and he absolutely loved it! I put a thick layer of Dijon to give an extra kick.
